terms.medium_def:
A man living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Num.1.9; 
only referred to as Helon (חֵלֹן); 
father of Eliab. § father of Eliab of the tribe of Zebulun

A man from the tribe of Levi living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.11; 
referred to as Merari or Merarite (מְרָרִי), or Merari or Merarite (מְרָרִי); 
son of Levi; 
a brother of Gershon, Kohath and Jochebed; 
father of Mahli, Mushi and Jaaziah. § the 3rd son of Levi and head of a Levitical family

A man from the tribe of Levi living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.11; 
referred to as Merari or Merarite (מְרָרִי), or Merari or Merarite (מְרָרִי); 
son of Levi; 
a brother of Gershon, Kohath and Jochebed; 
father of Mahli, Mushi and Jaaziah. § Merarites, of Marari "bitter"
descendants of Merari, the son of Levi, and members of a Levitical family

A woman living before Israel's Monarchy, first mentioned at Rut.1.2; 
referred to as Naomi (נׇעֳמִי), or Mara (מָרָא); 
wife of Elimelech; 
mother of Mahlon and Chilion. § a name that Naomi called herself due to her calamities

A man from the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of United Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Sa.9.1; 
only referred to as Zeror (צְרוֹר); 
a son of Becorath; 
father of Abiel. § grandfather of Ḳish

A location in Judah Tribe near Tekoa only mentioned at 1Ch.4.12; 
referred to as Ir-nahash (עִיר נָחָשׁ), or Ir-nahash (NIV= Ir Nahash) (=Alt tag) (עִיר נָחָשׁ); 
founded by Tehinnah - perhaps a person, the son of Tehinnah. §#A man of the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.4.12; 
son of: Tehinnah (H8468)

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.38.3; 
only referred to as Er (עֵר); 
son of Judah and Bath-shua; 
a brother of Onan and Shelah; 
half-brother of: Perez and Zerah; 
husband of Tamar.

A man from the tribe of Gad living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.16; 
referred to as Eri (עֵרִי), or Erite (עֵרִי); 
son of Gad; 
a brother of Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Arod and Areli. § son of Gad and progenitor of the family of Erites

A man living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.21.19; 
referred to as Jaare-oregim (יַעֲרֵי אֹרְגִים), or Jair (=Qere. Ketiv= Jaur) (יָעִיר); 
father of Elhanan.

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at 1Ch.4.21; 
only referred to as Er (עֵר); 
son of Shelah; 
a brother of Laadah, Jokim, Joash and Saraph; 
father or founder of Lecah.

A man from the tribe of Gad living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.16; 
referred to as Eri (עֵרִי), or Erite (עֵרִי); 
son of Gad; 
a brother of Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Arod and Areli. § Erites, of Eri "watchful"
descendants of Eri, the son of Gad

A man from the tribe of Ephraim living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at Num.26.36; 
referred to as Eran (עֵרָן), or Eranite (עֵרָנִי); 
son of Shuthelah; 
a brother of Bered. § the eldest son of Ephraim

A man from the tribe of Ephraim living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at Num.26.36; 
referred to as Eran (עֵרָן), or Eranite (עֵרָנִי); 
son of Shuthelah; 
a brother of Bered. § Eranites, of Eran "watcher"
the descendants of Eran, the son of Ephraim

A location in Edom first mentioned at Gen.14.7; 
referred to as Amalek or Amalekite or "valley" (KJV= Amalek) (עֲמָלֵק), or Amalekite (עֲמָלֵקִי). § people in southern Canaan
♣2) descendants of Amalek

A location in Edom first mentioned at Gen.14.7; 
referred to as Amalek or Amalekite or "valley" (KJV= Amalek) (עֲמָלֵק), or Amalekite (עֲמָלֵקִי). § Amalekite, of Amalek "people of lapping"
descendants of Amalek, the grandson of Esau

A man of the Edomites living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.36.12; 
only referred to as Amalek (עֲמָלֵק); 
son of Eliphaz and Timna; 
a brother of Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, Kenaz and Korah.

A man from the tribe of Asher living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.7.35; 
only referred to as Amal (עָמָל); 
son of Hotham; 
a brother of Zophah, Imna and Shelesh. § an Asherite, son of Helem
